	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="1. Start the game as a paladin.&#xD;&#xA;2. Become an oathbreaker (oe MakeOathbreaker with the paladin selected).&#xD;&#xA;3. End the day.&#xD;&#xA;4. End the next day too.&#xD;&#xA;5. Select a party member who is not a paladin and speak with the knight,&#xD;&#xA;OR&#xD;&#xA;1. oe CAMP_ForceOathbreakerKnight&#xD;&#xA;2. Go to camp. &#xD;&#xA;3. Select a party member who is not a paladin and speak with the knight," />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="2" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="When a player from a class other than a paladin tries to speak with the Oathbtreaker Knight he will not want to start a conversation.&#xD;&#xA;From design: Any non-paladin character talking to the Oathbreaker receives no reply. The Oathbreaker looks up at the character, but shakes their head - they have no interest in you." />
			<children>
